==English==

===Etymology===
{{OF.}} ''marault'': a [[vagabond]] through French.

=== Noun ===
{{en-noun}}
# Someone who moves about in roving fashion looking for plunder. (e.g. ''a band of marauders'')
# A band of outlaws who raids and pillages.
# By extension anything which [[maraud]]s.

